pollinate /ˈpɒlɪˌneɪt/

1. V-T To pollinate a plant or tree means to fertilize it with pollen. This is often done by insects. 给···传授花粉 

例： Many of the indigenous insects are needed to pollinate the local plants. 需要很多种土生昆虫给当地植物授粉。 

2. pollination N-UNCOUNT 

例： Without sufficient pollination, the growth of the corn is stunted. 没有充足的授粉，玉米的生长就会受阻。

